sue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Steps to reproduce\n\nGenerate a new app with Rails 7.1 and JRuby. The bundle will attempt to lock to the native platform (rather than the \"universal-java\" platform JRuby uses) preventing later gem installs from finding a match.\n\n```\n$ rails new demo\n      create  \n      create  README.md\n      create  Rakefile\n...\nResolving dependencies...\nFetching io-console 0.8.0 (java)\nFetching selenium-webdriver 4.31.0\nFetching rdoc 6.13.1\n...\n         run  bundle lock --add-platform=x86_64-linux\nWriting lockfile to /Users/headius/work/jruby/demo/Gemfile.lock\nFetching gem metadata from https://rubygems.org/.........\nCould not find gems matching 'activerecord-jdbcsqlite3-adapter' valid for all\nresolution platforms (universal-java-21, x86_64-linux) in rubygems repository\nhttps://rubygems.org/ or installed locally.\n...\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe application should generate and successfully resolve all dependencies.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nBecause the bundle is locked with a native platform, the `-java` gems for JRuby's ActiveRecord-JDBC adapters do not resolve successfully.\n\n### System configuration\n\n**Rails version**: 7.1.0\n\n**Ruby version**: JRuby 10 (Ruby 3.4 compatible)\n","closed_by":{"login":"rafaelfranca","id":47848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca","html_url":"https://github.com/rafaelfranca","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.gi